@DavidGeeraerts 
Those evaluation installation needs to be converted to the full version first before activation. You can do that with the change edition option in the MAS extras section. 

MVS/VLSC (subscription account downloads) server downloads come with the full version by default and you can activate them directly.

@JIGASHI 
W10 Enterprise LTSC 2021 and it's N version, both are not supported by HWID but you can use KMS38 or KMS option to activate.

However, the script will use IotEnterprise LTSC 2021 key to enable HWID activation. Script can't activate it's N version with HWID.

@julianmekato 

The online KMS renewal task already automatically creates a log file.
For activation or debug logs, you can use command line switches in the online KMS section.

@e-t-l you can get the key built into the motherboard license with this command. 

`wmic path softwarelicensingservice get oa3xoriginalproductkey`

MAS will show a prompt if it finds the system is already permanently activated.

