Though you can get a free 3-month trial. https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/security/defender-endpoint/microsoft-defender-endpoint?view=o365-worldwide

@WindowsAddict I  completely uninstalled Office (including running [OfficeScrubber](https://github.com/abbodi1406/WHD/raw/master/scripts/OfficeScrubber_11.7z)), then went to the Massgrave installer link https://massgrave.dev/office_c2r_links.html and downloaded the file with the 💓 emoji, labeled Office 365 ProPlus Online [x64]. The download link for that file is https://c2rsetup.officeapps.live.com/c2r/download.aspx?ProductreleaseID=O365ProPlusRetail&platform=x64&language=en-us&version=O16GA.

I ran the installer, and when it finished installing, **it had installed Office 2016**. I verified this with the MAS A-I-O script option 5 `Activation status` as well as checking Office registry data. 
I notice that the download link Massgrave provides ends with "&version=**O16**GA." Is there some possibility that this is installing Office 2016 versions of apps? Is there a way to force it to do otherwise?

No, it doesn't modify system files and open ports. 
You need to elaborate more on "Google Chrome gives me alarms about a malicious program." after KMS activation, share screenshots so we can better understand the issue. 
