Digital license transfer is not reliable; it theoretically works, but practically doesn't very often.
I would suggest not relying on it; just run the script again if you need to.

@mshakurov 
Each edition requires separate activation; your activation for the Home edition won't work on Pro.
Script is just telling you that you will need to activate it using the HWID option once the edition is changed.

@TEA-Time1 
- Office 2016/2019/2021/2024/O365 are all based on Office 16.0.
- If you installed Office 16.0 C2R, you can't have two update channels at the same time.
- If your objective is to have the latest updates for other Office apps and the last supported Publisher at the same time, then;
  - You can't have Office 2021 VL update channel, because that's not going to get any updates after Oct 2026.
  - The only possible way to achieve that is listed here https://github.com/massgravel/Microsoft-Activation-Scripts/discussions/1112#discussioncomment-14668975
- If you don't care about having the latest updates for other Office apps, and want the latest Publisher, then;
  - You can just disable updates on Sep 2026 on the current channel, or use the Office 2021 VL update channel.
- Ohook is fine for activation.

